text: Binboğa is a village in Afşin district of Kahramanmaraş Province, southern Turkey. Binboğa is located on the eastern side of Binboğa Mountains, west- northwest of Afşin and north-northwest of Kahramanmaraş. As of 2018, the population of the village was 235, decreasing from 303 in 2010. 303. ==References== Category:Afşin (district) Category:Villages in Kahramanmaraş Province
